1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
Hi, this is CellForge AI, a self-auditing research agent for green lithium-ion battery materials.

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:16,000
Battery researchers face too many papers, too many experimental claims, and too much risk of generating ideas that sound plausible but are not properly grounded.

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:24,000
CellForge AI is not a normal paper-search chatbot. It is a multi-step agent workflow.

4
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:35,000
It extracts structured claims, benchmarks retrieval, generates hypotheses, audits each hypothesis, traces the process with Arize, and exports an evidence-backed research proposal package.

5
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:44,000
For this demo, the scope is narrowed to green electrode materials and fabrication methods for lithium-ion batteries.

6
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:52,000
The agent reads Gemini Document Understanding extraction artifacts, builds a real evidence corpus, and generates five candidate research hypotheses.

7
00:00:52,000 --> 00:01:01,000
The key step is the evidence audit. Each hypothesis is scored for citation coverage, claim grounding, contradiction coverage, and evidence strength.

8
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:10,000
It is also scored for novelty gap, feasibility, and hallucination risk.

9
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:21,000
This is what makes CellForge AI different from a regular RAG assistant: it evaluates whether a proposed research direction is supported before recommending it.

10
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:30,000
In Arize AX, every major decision becomes inspectable.

11
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:39,000
The trace view shows evidence loading, retrieval, hypothesis generation, evaluator spans, and self-introspection.

12
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:48,000
The self-introspection stage selects hypothesis H003 because it has stronger grounding and lower hallucination risk than the alternatives.

13
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:57,000
The selected hypothesis is circular natural-graphite anodes with bio-based conductive surface repair.

14
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:09,000
It combines non-thermal plasma purification for natural or recycled graphite with a bio-derived carbon coating that may repair surface defects and stabilize the solid electrolyte interphase.

15
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:18,000
CellForge also keeps risk visible. For example, PHBV binder evidence shows strong cycling performance, but it uses chloroform and has lower adhesion than PVDF.

16
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Instead of ignoring this, the agent treats it as contradiction and risk-control evidence.

17
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:35,000
After the audit, CellForge applies a human validation gate.

18
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:40,000
In this demo, four critical claims are validated from Gemini Document Understanding artifacts and internal consistency checks.

19
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:48,000
Finally, Gemini Pro preview generates the research brief, and the repository exports a manuscript draft plus a molecular interface schematic.

20
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:54,000
The output is not an automatically publishable final paper. It is an evidence-backed research proposal package that a human researcher can validate, edit, and develop.

21
00:02:54,000 --> 00:03:00,000
CellForge AI starts with green battery materials because the future of clean energy, electric vehicles, and sustainable industry depends on better materials and cleaner battery manufacturing.
